cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the evolution of mobile cellular networks and proposes a new mode of radio access network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry theory to analyze the performance of the proposed mode, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper compares the performance of two different modes of radio access network in heterogeneous cellular networks, which is a topic of interest in communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers dynamic transmit power control in UL communication, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed mode in terms of system rate, spectrum efficiency, and energy efficiency, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
